{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Temporarily add a black section to the blue NHS logo for 2021.",
        "additional_details": "Black, Asian and other ethnic minority healthcare workers are vital to the NHS, even more so during the coronavirus pandemic.\r\n\r\nTragically, the numbers of BAME NHS staff killed by Covid-19 are proportionally much higher than mortality rates amongst their white colleagues.\r\n\r\nPublic Health England has also reported that non-white British NHS staff suffer discrimination at work.\r\n\r\nRecognising that black healthcare lives matter with a refreshed NHS logo will  show we care for them.",
        "background": "The NHS is a recognised and trusted UK brand.\r\n\r\nBut disproportionally high numbers of healthcare workers from Black, Asian and other ethnic minority backgrounds have died from Covid-19. \r\n\r\nAdding black to the blue NHS logo will provide a clear symbol of mourning for all healthcare heroes.",
